Yeah. If you say so.

1223
01:45:34,912 --> 01:45:38,958
Eskimo Joe's a quality nigger,
no doubt about it.

1224
01:45:40,000 --> 01:45:42,002
But if it was my money...

1225
01:45:42,962 --> 01:45:45,297
...I wouldn't pay no $12,000 for him.

1226
01:45:45,464 --> 01:45:47,633
What would your price be?

1227
01:45:47,800 --> 01:45:49,927
Well, if I was inclined
to be generous...

1228
01:45:50,094 --> 01:45:53,806
...and I don't know why I would be
inclined to be generous...

1229
01:45:54,390 --> 01:45:56,183
...9000.

1230
01:45:56,600 --> 01:45:57,643
Maybe.

1231
01:45:58,769 --> 01:45:59,812
Dr. Schultz...

1232
01:46:00,771 --> 01:46:04,775
...let me reclarify how this
whole negotiation came about.

1233
01:46:04,942 --> 01:46:07,319
It wasn't me who came to you
to sell a nigger.

1234
01:46:07,486 --> 01:46:08,529
Sure wasn't.

1235
01:46:08,696 --> 01:46:10,990
-You approached me to buy one.
-Sure was.

1236
01:46:11,156 --> 01:46:13,576
That $9000 Bright Boy's
been bandying about...

1237
01:46:13,742 --> 01:46:17,079
...ain't too far off. If I wanted
to sell Eskimo Joe for that...

1238
01:46:17,246 --> 01:46:19,957
-...I could do so any day of the week.
-Any day.

1239
01:46:20,124 --> 01:46:24,461
But like you said in Greenville, doctor,
I don't wanna sell him.

1240
01:46:24,795 --> 01:46:28,966
It was only your ridiculous offer
of $12,000...

1241
01:46:29,133 --> 01:46:31,802
...that made me even consider it.

1242
01:46:40,144 --> 01:46:44,273
You know, Monsieur Candie, you do
possess the power of persuasion.

1243
01:46:48,569 --> 01:46:50,738
Why not?
Monsieur Candie, you have a deal.

1244
01:46:50,905 --> 01:46:53,032
Eskimo Joe, $12,000.

1245
01:46:53,198 --> 01:46:56,285
Hooray, doctor. Hooray.
And a wise decision that is.

1246
01:46:56,452 --> 01:47:00,122
However, that is a tremendous
amount of money.

1247
01:47:00,289 --> 01:47:03,334
And the way you have your Mr. Moguy,
I have a lawyer.

1248
01:47:03,500 --> 01:47:05,294
Persnickety man named Tuttle.

1249
01:47:05,461 --> 01:47:08,631
And I would need my Mr. Tuttle
to draw up a legal contract...

1250
01:47:08,797 --> 01:47:12,676
...before I'd feel comfortable exchanging
that amount of money for flesh.

1251
01:47:12,843 --> 01:47:16,639
Not to mention having Eskimo Joe
examined by a physician of my choosing.

1252
01:47:16,805 --> 01:47:22,435
-Naturally.
-So, say I return in about...

1253
01:47:24,563 --> 01:47:25,731
...five days' time.

1254
01:47:25,898 --> 01:47:27,024
Five days?

1255
01:47:27,191 --> 01:47:28,441
With my Mr. Tuttle.

1256
01:47:28,609 --> 01:47:30,903
And then my Mr. Tuttle
and your Mr. Moguy...

1257
01:47:31,070 --> 01:47:33,822
...can hash out the finer details
between themselves.

1258
01:47:34,573 --> 01:47:37,493
I say splendid, doctor. Splendid.

1259
01:47:38,243 --> 01:47:39,495
Gentlemen...

1260
01:47:40,537 --> 01:47:42,915
...may I propose a toast?

1261
01:47:44,792 --> 01:47:46,418
To Eskimo Joe.

1262
01:47:46,585 --> 01:47:50,589
Or shall we call him
the Black Hercules?

1263
01:47:50,756 --> 01:47:52,675
To the Black Hercules.

1264
01:47:52,841 --> 01:47:54,426
The Black Hercules.

1265
01:47:54,593 --> 01:47:55,803
To the Black Hercules.

1266
01:47:55,970 --> 01:47:59,472
You was right, doctor.
That name do have "pan-ass."

1267
01:48:01,558 --> 01:48:04,979
Hildi, top my drink off.

1268
01:48:07,773 --> 01:48:12,444
So, Hildi, how you like serving
at the big table in the Big House, huh?

1269
01:48:12,903 --> 01:48:16,115
When Monsieur Candie talk to you,
you answers.

1270
01:48:16,281 --> 01:48:18,450
I like it a lot, Monsieur Candie.

1271
01:48:19,243 --> 01:48:22,371
Better than sizzling in that hot box
or dragging your ass...

1272
01:48:22,538 --> 01:48:23,664
...through a bramble bush.

1273
01:48:23,831 --> 01:48:27,626
Maybe not as much fun as getting to
pleasure all them Mandingos, huh?

1274
01:48:27,793 --> 01:48:30,170
-She like them niggers. Sure do.
-Like Samson?

1275
01:48:30,337 --> 01:48:31,380
No, sir.

1276
01:48:31,547 --> 01:48:33,090
You know, Monsieur Candie...

1277
01:48:33,257 --> 01:48:36,969
...the doctor here might be interested
in seeing Hildi's peeled back...

1278
01:48:37,136 --> 01:48:40,513
...seeing as how they don't have
many niggers where he come from.

1279
01:48:40,681 --> 01:48:43,017
Dr. Schultz,
when you was alone with Hildi...

1280
01:48:43,183 --> 01:48:46,395
...did you just speak German
or did you take her clothes off?

1281
01:48:46,562 --> 01:48:50,107
-No, we just talked and--
-Oh, so you haven't seen her back?

1282
01:48:50,274 --> 01:48:51,316
I haven't--

1283
01:48:51,483 --> 01:48:54,653
No, no, no. Stephen's right,
you might find this interesting.

1284
01:48:54,820 --> 01:48:56,238
Hildi, take off your dress.

1285
01:48:56,405 --> 01:48:58,407
Show Dr. Schultz your back here.
Go on.

1286
01:48:58,574 --> 01:49:02,244
Calvin, I just got her all dressed up
and looking nice.

1287
01:49:02,411 --> 01:49:05,372
But, Lara Lee,
Dr. Schultz is from Düsseldorf.

1288
01:49:05,538 --> 01:49:08,375
They don't got niggers there.
He is a man of medicine.

1289
01:49:08,541 --> 01:49:11,462
It would fascinate him,
the niggers' endurance for pain.

1290
01:49:11,628 --> 01:49:14,965
These niggers are tough, Dr. Schultz,
no doubt about it.

1291
01:49:15,132 --> 01:49:17,176
Hildi's got something like four lashes.

1292
01:49:17,342 --> 01:49:20,012
Lara Lee just get one,
she'd lose her goddamn mind.

1293
01:49:20,179 --> 01:49:23,474
-Look at that, doctor. It's like a painting.
-Calvin!

1294
01:49:24,224 --> 01:49:27,560
We are eating. Ain't no one
wanna look at her whipped-up back.

1295
01:49:29,188 --> 01:49:31,273
Fine. Fine, fine, fine.

1296
01:49:31,523 --> 01:49:34,567
After dinner, then, Stephen.
After dinner.

1297
01:49:35,235 --> 01:49:37,237
During the brandies, gentlemen.

1298
01:49:43,243 --> 01:49:45,412
Cora, come get this girl.

1299
01:49:48,332 --> 01:49:51,293
-She a mess.
-Yes, ma'am?

1300
01:49:51,668 --> 01:49:55,839
Why are you all undone?
I just got you done up. Come on in here.

1301
01:50:02,054 --> 01:50:05,974
Baby, you on Stephen bad side,
and you need to be on his blind side.

1302
01:50:06,141 --> 01:50:08,644
You say you ain't know him.

1303
01:50:10,437 --> 01:50:16,276
I said, you said you ain't know him.

1304
01:50:17,319 --> 01:50:18,821
I don't.

1305
01:50:19,363 --> 01:50:20,948
Yes, you do.

1306
01:50:22,866 --> 01:50:24,118
Mr. Stephen...

1307
01:50:25,452 --> 01:50:26,578
...I don't.

1308
01:50:26,870 --> 01:50:29,540
Why is you lying to me?

1309
01:50:31,500 --> 01:50:32,918
I ain't.

1310
01:50:33,252 --> 01:50:35,504
Then why is you crying?

1311
01:50:36,088 --> 01:50:37,923
You scaring me.

1312
01:50:38,132 --> 01:50:39,341
Why is I'm scaring you?

1313
01:50:40,134 --> 01:50:42,010
Because you scary.

1314
01:50:43,554 --> 01:50:46,223
To speak German this afternoon
with Hildi...

1315
01:50:46,390 --> 01:50:50,060
...was positively soul-enriching.

1316
01:50:50,269 --> 01:50:52,938
Doctor, that warms my heart
to hear that.

1317
01:50:53,105 --> 01:50:56,358
You stay right here.

1318
01:51:01,488 --> 01:51:06,034
You indicated earlier
you'd be willing to part with Hildi.

1319
01:51:06,201 --> 01:51:09,288
Why, yes. Yes, sirree, Bob, I did.

1320
01:51:10,914 --> 01:51:12,791
In that case...

1321
01:51:12,958 --> 01:51:16,962
...allow me to propose
another proposition.

1322
01:51:17,129 --> 01:51:18,255
I'm all ears.

1323
01:51:18,422 --> 01:51:20,507
Hurry up, goddamn it!

1324
01:51:20,883 --> 01:51:22,426
-Monsieur Candie--
-Stephen.

1325
01:51:23,510 --> 01:51:26,388
You just interrupted Dr. Schultz here.

1326
01:51:27,222 --> 01:51:32,060
I'm sorry, Dr. Schultz.
My ears ain't worth a damn these days.

1327
01:51:32,227 --> 01:51:33,353
Excuse him.

1328
01:51:33,520 --> 01:51:37,024
Monsieur Candie, could I get
a word with you in the kitchen?

1329
01:51:37,608 --> 01:51:39,484
You mean get up out of my chair?

1330
01:51:39,651 --> 01:51:41,653
If'n you could manage it.

1331
01:51:41,820 --> 01:51:44,823
-Why?
-It's about dessert.

1332
01:51:44,990 --> 01:51:46,783
What about dessert?

1333
01:51:46,950 --> 01:51:49,536
I'd rather discuss that in private.

1334
01:51:49,702 --> 01:51:51,872
We're having white cake.

1335
01:51:52,039 --> 01:51:54,374
What sort of melodrama
could be brewing?

1336
01:51:54,541 --> 01:51:58,879
You right, Monsieur Candie.
You right. I'll handle it myself.

1337
01:51:59,046 --> 01:52:00,380
Meet me in the library.

1338
01:52:00,547 --> 01:52:03,926
I just can't understand
why you won't come talk to these niggers.

1339
01:52:04,092 --> 01:52:06,428
Shit get fucked up around here,
you blame me.

1340
01:52:06,595 --> 01:52:11,225
Fine, fine. Friend Stephen,
I will be along momentarily.

1341
01:52:11,391 --> 01:52:12,893
Yes, sir.

1342
01:52:13,435 --> 01:52:16,855
Well, gentlemen, as you can see...

1343
01:52:17,022 --> 01:52:19,191
...talented as they are in the kitchen...

1344
01:52:19,358 --> 01:52:22,945
...from time to time,
adult supervision is required.

1345
01:52:25,781 --> 01:52:28,075
If you'll excuse me a moment....

1346
01:52:33,664 --> 01:52:35,707
You may clear the dinner service.

1347
01:52:36,959 --> 01:52:38,919
You heard him. Go on, get.

1348
01:52:39,795 --> 01:52:40,837
Hurry up, girl.

1349
01:52:41,004 --> 01:52:46,093
So, Dr. Schultz, why don't you
regale us with a tale of the circus?

1350
01:52:46,260 --> 01:52:48,929
-The circus?
-Yes.

1351
01:52:55,310 --> 01:52:57,312
What is the matter?

1352
01:53:02,401 --> 01:53:07,489
Them motherfuckers ain't here
to buy no Mandingos.

1353
01:53:07,656 --> 01:53:09,199
They wants that girl.

1354
01:53:11,285 --> 01:53:13,996
Stephen, what the hell
are you talking about?

1355
01:53:14,162 --> 01:53:17,499
They playing your ass for a fool
is what I'm talking about.

1356
01:53:17,833 --> 01:53:21,336
They ain't here
for no muscle-bound Jimmie.

1357
01:53:21,920 --> 01:53:24,006
They here for that girl.

1358
01:53:24,381 --> 01:53:26,466
What girl? What, Hildi?

1359
01:53:26,633 --> 01:53:30,262
Yeah, Hildi. Her and Django,
them niggers know each other.

1360
01:53:31,930 --> 01:53:33,515
He just bought Eskimo Joe.

1361
01:53:33,682 --> 01:53:36,143
-Did he give you any money?
-No, not yet, but--

1362
01:53:36,310 --> 01:53:38,687
Then he ain't bought diddly.
Not yet, no how.

1363
01:53:38,854 --> 01:53:41,148
But he's just about to buy...

1364
01:53:41,315 --> 01:53:44,443
...who he come here to buy
when I interrupted him.

1365
01:53:44,609 --> 01:53:48,238
"Thank you, Stephen."
You're welcome, Calvin.

1366
01:53:52,951 --> 01:53:55,495
Where you getting all this?

1367
01:53:56,163 --> 01:53:59,958
Why would they go through all that
for a nigger with a chewed-up back...

1368
01:54:00,125 --> 01:54:01,251
...ain't worth $300?

1369
01:54:01,418 --> 01:54:05,047
They doing it because that nigger
Django's in love with Hildi.

1370
01:54:05,213 --> 01:54:06,381
She probably his wife.

1371
01:54:07,215 --> 01:54:11,303
Why that German gives a fuck who
that uppity son of a bitch is in love with...

1372
01:54:11,470 --> 01:54:13,638
...I'm sure I don't know.

1373
01:54:16,016 --> 01:54:18,060
If she's who they want...

1374
01:54:18,393 --> 01:54:22,689
...why this whole snake oil pitch
about Mandingos then?

1375
01:54:22,855 --> 01:54:26,401
You wouldn't pay no never mind
to no $300.

1376
01:54:26,610 --> 01:54:28,904
But that 12,000?

1377
01:54:29,488 --> 01:54:32,407
That made you real friendly,
now, didn't it?

1378
01:54:34,659 --> 01:54:36,870
Yes, it did.

1379
01:54:39,706 --> 01:54:41,708
His wife, huh?

1380
01:54:45,253 --> 01:54:49,549
If it had been a snake,
it would have bit me.

1381
01:54:52,302 --> 01:54:54,888
Those lying...

1382
01:54:55,180 --> 01:54:58,517
...goddamn time-wasting...

1383
01:54:58,683 --> 01:55:01,561
...sons of bitches.

1384
01:55:03,188 --> 01:55:04,564
Sons of bitches!

1385
01:55:04,731 --> 01:55:10,570
--out of New Orleans, so I have quite
a bit of practice with theater types.

1386
01:55:11,154 --> 01:55:12,572
Oh, there you are.

1387
01:55:12,739 --> 01:55:16,410
I was beginning to think that you
and that old crow run off together.

1388
01:55:17,411 --> 01:55:19,663
That'd be a hell of a note, wouldn't it?

1389
01:55:20,122 --> 01:55:22,749
Lara Lee, I was just looking
out the big window.

1390
01:55:22,916 --> 01:55:25,919
Billy Crash is out there
dealing with some shady slaver...

1391
01:55:26,086 --> 01:55:31,133
...trying to sell a passel of ponies.
Be a dear, go give them gals an eyeball.

1392
01:55:31,425 --> 01:55:34,219
-Of course, brother.
-Thank you, darling.

1393
01:55:47,023 --> 01:55:50,485
Yeah. Business never sleeps.

1394
01:55:52,571 --> 01:55:55,449
Apropos, before your exit...

1395
01:55:55,615 --> 01:55:59,911
...we were discussing the possibility
of my purchasing Broomhilda.

1396
01:56:00,078 --> 01:56:02,914
Yes. Yes, we were, doctor.

1397
01:56:03,081 --> 01:56:05,250
And we will again, in a moment.

1398
01:56:21,516 --> 01:56:23,935
Who's your little friend?

1399
01:56:28,732 --> 01:56:30,525
This is Ben.

1400
01:56:31,568 --> 01:56:36,490
He's a old Joe that lived around here
for a long time.

1401
01:56:36,740 --> 01:56:39,201
And I do mean a long damn time.

1402
01:56:40,327 --> 01:56:44,456
Old Ben here took care of my daddy...

1403
01:56:44,748 --> 01:56:46,917
...and my daddy's daddy.

1404
01:56:47,083 --> 01:56:49,920
Till he up and keeled over one day...

1405
01:56:52,464 --> 01:56:54,716
...Old Ben took care of me.

1406
01:56:56,593 --> 01:57:00,680
Growing up the son of a huge
plantation owner in Mississippi...

1407
01:57:00,847 --> 01:57:02,682
...puts a white man in contact...

1408
01:57:02,849 --> 01:57:06,520
...with a whole lot of black faces.

1409
01:57:08,271 --> 01:57:13,693
I spent my whole life here,
right here in Candyland...

1410
01:57:14,861 --> 01:57:18,615
...surrounded by black faces.

1411
01:57:20,617 --> 01:57:24,079
Now, seeing them every day,
day in, day out...

1412
01:57:24,246 --> 01:57:26,706
...I only had one question:

1413
01:57:29,918 --> 01:57:31,294
Why don't they kill us?

1414
01:57:35,507 --> 01:57:40,595
Now, right out there on that porch,
three times a week for 50 years...

1415
01:57:40,762 --> 01:57:45,767
...Old Ben here would shave my daddy
with a straight razor.

1416
01:57:46,142 --> 01:57:51,064
Now, if I was Old Ben, I would have
cut my daddy's goddamn throat...

1417
01:57:51,231 --> 01:57:55,110
...and it wouldn't have taken me
no 50 years to do it, neither.

1418
01:57:57,195 --> 01:57:59,114
But he never did.

1419
01:58:00,615 --> 01:58:01,741
Why not?

1420
01:58:03,243 --> 01:58:07,664
You see, the science of phrenology...

1421
01:58:08,206 --> 01:58:10,375
...is crucial to understanding...

1422
01:58:10,542 --> 01:58:13,795
...the separation of our two species.

1423
01:58:15,130 --> 01:58:18,091
In the skull of the African here...

1424
01:58:18,883 --> 01:58:21,428
...the area associated
with submissiveness...

1425
01:58:21,595 --> 01:58:27,392
...is larger than any human or any other
subhuman species on planet Earth.

1426
01:58:42,324 --> 01:58:44,534
If you examine...

1427
01:58:45,577 --> 01:58:48,330
...this piece of skull here...

1428
01:58:54,044 --> 01:58:57,631
...you will notice three distinct dimples.

1429
01:59:01,176 --> 01:59:05,055
Here, here and here.

1430
01:59:05,221 --> 01:59:06,431
Now...

1431
01:59:06,598 --> 01:59:11,478
...if I was holding the skull
of an Isaac Newton or Galileo...

1432
01:59:11,645 --> 01:59:16,066
...these three dimples would be found
in the area most associated with...

1433
01:59:16,232 --> 01:59:18,026
...creativity.

1434
01:59:18,193 --> 01:59:20,695
But this is the skull of Old Ben.

1435
01:59:20,945 --> 01:59:22,822
And in the skull of Old Ben...

1436
01:59:22,989 --> 01:59:25,283
...unburdened by genius...

1437
01:59:25,450 --> 01:59:30,288
...these three dimples exist in the area
of the skull most associated with...

1438
01:59:30,747 --> 01:59:32,457
...servility.

1439
01:59:33,291 --> 01:59:35,293
Now, Bright Boy...

1440
01:59:35,752 --> 01:59:38,129
...I will admit you are pretty clever.

1441
01:59:40,465 --> 01:59:43,176
But if I took this hammer here...

1442
01:59:44,719 --> 01:59:47,639
...and I bashed in your skull with it...

1443
01:59:48,098 --> 01:59:53,895
...you would have the same
three dimples in the same place...

1444
01:59:54,646 --> 01:59:56,189
...as Old Ben.

1445
01:59:57,315 --> 02:00:00,777
Hey! Now lay your palms
flat on that tabletop!

1446
02:00:00,944 --> 02:00:03,947
If you lift those palms
off that turtle shell tabletop...

1447
02:00:04,114 --> 02:00:07,701
...Mr. Pooch is gonna let loose
with both barrels of that sawed-off.

1448
02:00:08,535 --> 02:00:11,913
There have been a lot of lies
around this dinner table tonight...

1449
02:00:12,080 --> 02:00:14,207
...but that you can believe!

1450
02:00:14,374 --> 02:00:19,838
Mr. Moguy, would you collect the pistol
hanging off these boys' hips here?

1451
02:00:24,259 --> 02:00:27,470
-Thank you ever so much.
-Doctor.

1452
02:00:31,307 --> 02:00:33,184
Where were we?

1453
02:00:37,147 --> 02:00:39,107
Jackass.

1454
02:00:42,444 --> 02:00:44,070
Yes.

1455
02:00:44,237 --> 02:00:47,782
I do believe you were just getting ready
to make me a proposition...

1456
02:00:47,949 --> 02:00:49,617
...to buy Broomhilda.

1457
02:00:49,784 --> 02:00:51,411
Am I right?

1458
02:00:55,206 --> 02:00:56,791
Right.

1459
02:00:58,626 --> 02:00:59,669
Bring out Hildi!

1460
02:01:03,339 --> 02:01:05,216
Get over there yonder.

